The measure `E_{a,x,y}` is constructed using the Riesz-Markov-Kakutani theorem from the linear functional `f ↦ ⟨x, f(a)y⟩`, where `f(a)` is defined via the continuous functional calculus. The linearity of the integral in the measure is a fundamental property we expect from an integral. 

